<dl id="un1013bk"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013bk"> (NLI.3) 13(bk)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> spleen <font color="green">[sketch of symbol]</font> sun</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The third centre, at <mark>the spleen</mark>, gives the effect of six petals or undulations, and it seems that all of these are concerned in the specialisation, subdivision and dispersion of the vitality which comes to us from the sun. Presumably for that reason this centre is especially radiant, glowing and <mark>sun-like</mark>. <small> <a name="THmay1910" href="/udra/udex.htm#thmay1910"><cite title="source">The Theosophist</cite></a> (May 1910), C.W. Leadbeater, &ldquo;FORCE-CENTRES AND THE SERPENT-FIRE&rdquo; p. 1077f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Possibly copied to missing notesheet.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c07259i" href="../../../f/ff/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07259i">VI.C.07:259(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
